[{"id":29890,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f5fe9d98-9eb3-412a-8ef5-79920934ef00-image.png\" style=\"width: 184px; height: 105px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/95c64d4b-f70c-49a8-9e3e-cb23a5e0e8f2-image.png\" style=\"width: 87px; height: 89px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7a653a94-76bc-4e1e-9873-a41aa3c5e4f5-image.png\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 106px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bbe9467c-223d-4d50-9b34-dbf2f3d161a7-image.png\" style=\"width: 89px; height: 103px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/27487a9f-324b-4b49-a5b9-04444fb980eb-image.png\" style=\"width: 307px; height: 99px;\" /></p><p>It exists as non-planar tab-shaped so it is non aromatic.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29860,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> (Solid)","U.V. Light","Visualisation agent as a component of mobile phase","Spraying of an appropriate reagent"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Thin Layer Chromatography is a technique used to isolate non-volatile mixtures. The experiment is conducted on a sheet of aluminium foil, plastic, or glass which is coated with a thin layer of adsorbent material. The material usually used is aluminium oxide, cellulose, or silica gel.</p><p>The sample spots can be observed under a UV light chamber,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;solid or by spraying of an appropriate reagent which can react with the sample spot.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":29793,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c08331a2-3757-462d-8a5e-048623e944e6.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 145px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1e207d72-1b78-40c9-bb51-997c7ce628ee.png\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 148px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ff2ccf7d-7ea0-4c0d-81e1-9720f5b0b881.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 153px;\"/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3880ae41-8fdb-4990-982c-6bb86af3de69.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 119px;\"/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Acidic hydrogen is a hydrogen atom in an acid that dissociates to generate a positive ion.</p><p>After removal of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>ion, the negative charge is formed. The more stable the negative charge, the more will be the acidic strength.</p><p>Due to cross conjugation of negative charge, it is<br/>most stabilised anion.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0605b598-81f8-49ea-bcaa-e76574a293c2.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 379px;\"/></p><p>Hence, the answer is option D.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":29910,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>)</mo></math> only","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>)</mo></math> only","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> only","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></math> only"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> only in Resonance</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7b77891c-b696-45fd-a48c-4367779ddc4e-image.png\" style=\"width: 311px; height: 422px;\" /></p><p>In&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and</mtext><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;positive charge is not in conjugation therefore resonance is not possible in these.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":29674,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["(A)-(IV), (B)-(III), (C)-(II), (D)-(I)","(A)-(I), (B)-(II), (C)-(III), (D)-(IV)","(A)-(III), (B)-(IV), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)","(A)-(II), (B)-(I), (C)-(IV), (D)-(III)"],"answer":0,"solution":"(A) Aniline $-\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}$ : Steam Distillation<br />(B) Glycerol from spent-lye in soap industry - Distillation under reduced pressure<br />(C) Different fraction of crude oil in petroleum industry - Fractional distillation<br />(D) $\\mathrm{CHCl}_3-$ Aniline - Simple distillation","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29874,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/58ce1ef2-0882-4d78-a20d-4f3a21002a3a-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 193px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/694138fb-3c53-4a2e-bf01-c0c8c3fb1f18-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 196px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/96e5e5a7-0441-402b-9633-00a734d1304d-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 180px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/32f7b045-c748-4048-939e-344905e6431d-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 196px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>A staggered conformation is a chemical conformation of an ethane-like molecule in which the substituents are at the maximum distance from each other. This requires the torsional angle to be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/694138fb-3c53-4a2e-bf01-c0c8c3fb1f18-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 196px;\" /></p><p>In anti conformation the dihedral angle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>180</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math> (maximum)</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":29933,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nitro-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>-hydroxymethyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>-amino benzaldehyde","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>-amino-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>-hydroxymethyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>-nitrogenzaldehyde","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>-amino-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>-hydroxymethyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nitrobenzaldehyde","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>-amino-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-formyl-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>-hydroxymethyl nitrogenzene"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/53bd09ff-a9e7-41a7-9e80-636400388fa6-image.png\" style=\"width: 181px; height: 167px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>-Amino-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>-(hydroxymethyl)-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>-nitro benzene carbaldehyde.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29928,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#62;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Presence of electron withdrawing groups such as nitro group enhance the acidic strength of phenol and the presence of electron releasing groups such as alkyl group decreases the acidic strength of phenol.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/79cdad86-d411-4319-8eaf-8fde8c0b8f78-image.png\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 111px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29681,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{MF}=\\mathrm{C}_9 \\mathrm{H}_{12}$<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Yg5fdOPUO8DSpOM6ws60b9tivHy3FRu19En8K9JU3mY.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29736,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["2-formyl-4-hydroxyhept-7-enoic acid","2-formyl-4-hydroxyhept-6-enoic acid","2-carboxy-4-hydroxyhept-7-enal","2-carboxy-4-hydroxyhept-6-enal"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/j9-qijJGRFLe4zBZpKF07avzy0Dq9F0OPu0PoEG6of4.original.fullsize.png\"><br />2-formly-4-hydroxyhept-6-enoic acid","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":30067,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["The $\\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{O}$ bond is weaker than the $\\mathrm{C}-\\mathrm{O}$ bond","The anion $\\mathrm{HCOO}^{-}$has two resonating structures","The anion is obtained by removal of a proton from the acid molecule","Electronic orbitals of carbon atom are hybridised"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/tvHhHbT83EFpWYWlZiLhWebWbu1DVhWWVGQ-Ni_KdGs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":29697,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Mass of organic compound $=0.25 \\mathrm{~g}$\nMass of $\\mathrm{AgBr}=0.15 \\mathrm{~g}$\nNo. of moles of $\\mathrm{Br}=$ No. of moles of $\\mathrm{AgBr}=\\frac{0.15}{188}$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { Mass of } \\mathrm{Br}=\\frac{0.15 \\times 80}{188} \\mathrm{~g} \\\\\n& \\% \\text { of } \\mathrm{Br}=\\frac{0.15 \\times 80 \\times 100}{188 \\times 0.25} \\\\\n& =25.5 \\% \\\\\n& =255 \\times 10^{-1} \\%\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (24 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":29996,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>dimethyl</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>pentene</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>dimethylpent</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>ene</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Isopropyl</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>butene</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>dimethyl</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>pentene</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cc.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 61px;\" /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/image3-1a36bceb-2890-42fd-a548-61ee2b851b67.jpg\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/neo11.png\" style=\"width: 220px; height: 140px;\" /><br /><br />Hydrocarbon of 7 carbons having neopentyl and a vinyl group.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":29962,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"General Organic Chemistry","question":"","options":["<math><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></math>","<math><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"norma